<p>Boolean literals should be avoided in comparison expressions <code>==</code> and <code>!=</code> to improve code readability.</p>
<p>This rule also reports on redundant boolean operations.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
let someValue = "0";
// ...

if (someValue == true) { /* ... */ }
if (someBooleanValue != true) { /* ... */ }
doSomething(!false);
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
if (someValue &amp;&amp; someValue != "0") { /* ... */ }
if (!someBooleanValue) { /* ... */ }
doSomething(true);
</pre>